com.wx.util.representables

Interface TypeCaster<InType,OutType>

  • Type Parameters:
    InType - First type
    OutType - Second type
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanRepr, CharRepr, DirectoryRepr, DoubleRepr, EncodedBytesRepr, EncryptedRepr, EnumCaster, EnumCasterLC, FileRepr, FloatRepr, IntRepr, ListRepr, LongRepr, MapRepr, NullSafeCaster, PairRepr, SetRepr, StringRepr

    public interface TypeCaster<InType,OutType>
    This interface allows to cast any type into any other and vice-versa.

    Note that most implementation do not allow to cast null values. If that is needed, any caster can be enforced to cast null values by using nullable().

      • nullable

        default TypeCaster<InType,OutType> nullable()
        Creates a wrapper of this caster that allows to cast null values. Casting a null value (in any direction) will always yield a null value.

        Note: Some casters already allow to cast null values, in such case, this method will return the same caster.

        Returns:
        The same caster enhanced with the possibility of casting null
